This column represents the earliest possible date that a problem could have been diagnosed on. The latest possible date is in PROB_DX_MAX_DATE. If these values are the same, then the date is exact rather than fuzzy. For a problem or condition affecting a patient, the diagnosis date is defined as the date when a qualified professional first recognized the presence of that condition with sufficient certainty, regardless of whether it was fully characterized at that time. For diseases such as cancer, this may be the earliest date of a clinical diagnosis from before it was histologically confirmed, not the date of confirmation if that occurred later.
